the condition that you can flip any substring >=k means that you can flip any elements in [0,n-k-1] and [k,n]. if 2k<=n, two intervals are overlapped, we can always flip every elements of the string. Otherwise, [n-k, k-1] should consist of same elements. find the largest k for that.

    s='110111'
    ct,n=set(),len(s)
    for k in range(n//2+1,n+1):
        ct|={s[n-k],s[k-1]}
        if len(ct)==2:
            return k-1
    return n
